g.desc: Neighborhoods provide a grouping mechanism for restricting th...
g.text: Neighborhoods provide a grouping mechanism for restricting the visibility of ALAs with respect to each other (i.e. individual ALAs only interact with ALAs in the same neighborhood).

g.title: Sheet.214
g.desc: A package is a defined set of FUNITs that work together to pr...
g.text: A package is a defined set of FUNITs that work together to provide specific domain application functionality. For example, the Std-Coral package defines the minimum set of FUNITs for a CORAL compliant ALA Packages are organized by Domains (i.e. the Std-Coral package is in part of the ‘Std’ domain). All domains have a single owner, A owner can be a individual, company, trade organization, committee, etc. For example, the Std domain owner is the SW-Eden open source project.
